sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Files With System Process Name In Unsuspected Locations
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of an executable with a system process name in folders other than the system ones (System32, SysWOW64...etc).
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Sander Wiebing, Tim Shelton, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects instances of svchost.exe running with an unusual or uncommon command line parameter by excluding known legitimate or common patterns.
This could point at a file masquerading as svchost, a process injection, or hollowing of a legitimate svchost instance.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Python Image Load By Non-Python Process
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the image load of "Python Core" by a non-Python process. This might be indicative of a Python script bundled with Py2Exe.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Patrick St. John, OTR (Open Threat Research)

match_context.values: @{EventID=7; Product=Python; ImageLoaded=C:\Users\george\AppData\Local\Temp\_MEI77882\python310.dll; Description=Python Core; Company=Python Software Foundation; Signed=true; SignatureStatus=Valid; Signature=Python Software Foundation; Hashes=SHA1=ADA39F10EF0BBDCF05822F4260E43D53367B0017,MD5=E4533934B37E688106BEAC6C5919281E,SHA256=2BF761BAE584BA67D9A41507B45EBD41AB6AE51755B1782496D0BC60CC1D41D5,IMPHASH=1BA87C09C523D7DE2B8992A559808C95; Image=C:\Users\george\Desktop\file.exe; OriginalFileName=python310.dll; FileVersion=3.10.10}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Disable Internal Tools or Feature in Registry
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects registry modifications that change features of internal Windows tools (malware like Agent Tesla uses this technique)
Detects script file execution (.js, .jse, .vba, .vbe, .vbs, .wsf) by Wscript/Cscript
Detects potential DLL sideloading of Python DLL files.

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Files With System Process Name In Unsuspected Locations
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description:
Detects the creation of an executable with a system process name in folders other than the system ones (System32, SysWOW64, etc.).
It is highly recommended to perform an initial baseline before using this rule in production.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Sander Wiebing, Tim Shelton, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)
